<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE & OUT; NITTY-GRITTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times-Post News Service 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Prevent messy spills when children are painting. Cut a hole in center of a 
sponge and place over paint jar. This will keep the container from spilling 
over and it will also catch drips. 
</P>
<P>
 * Periodically apply lemon oil to wicker furniture to prevent it from drying 
out. 
</P>
<P>
 * When trying to remove paper from wood surfaces, apply a few drops of salad 
oil on the paper. Let set until paper can be rubbed away with a soft cloth. 
Repeat procedure if necessary. 
</P>
<P>
 * Store out-of-season clothes in fresh plastic trash can with lid. This will 
keep moths and humidity out. 
</P>
<P>
 * Try storing plastic wrap in refrigerator. This will keep it from sticking 
together when you want to tear off a sheet. 
</P>
<P>
 * To remove musty odors from an old trunk, place a coffee can filled with 
cat-box deodorizer inside the trunk overnight. 
</P>
<P>
 * When cutting fresh flowers from the garden, pick in the morning before the 
heat affects the blooms. Plunge freshly cut stems into a bucket of warm water, 
arrange and enjoy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
