REALIGNMENT MEANS A BREEZE FOR DODGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Dodgers have a good team, and this is usually the part of the season in 
which we get to see if they can take the next step and become a great team that 
contends for a division title. 
</P>
<P>
 Well, this year, thanks to realignment and the added playoff teams, it doesn't 
look like they will have to take any steps and could possibly win the division 
title. Welcome to the '90s. Just think, it's only a matter of time before we 
root, root, root for the Dodgers to be the first eighth-seeded team to beat a 
No. 1 seed. 
