<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJOR LEAGUES; TURNER HAS HODGKIN'S DISEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cleveland Indians have learned that reliever Matt Turner, 27, has 
Hodgkin's disease. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner underwent surgery Tuesday in Cleveland to remove swollen lymph nodes in 
the groin area, and tests revealed Friday that they were malignant. He is 
facing up to eight months of chemotherapy, John Hart, Indian general manager, 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Philadelphia pitcher Tommy Greene probably will be out a month because of an 
injured right shoulder. . . . Pitcher Charlie Leibrandt, 37, cut off his 
comeback attempt with the Kansas City Royals. 
</P>
