<HEADLINE>
<P>
KINGS SAY PLAYOFF REFUNDS COMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Kings announced Friday that they are in the process of issuing 
playoff-ticket refunds to season-seat subscribers. 
</P>
<P>
 Payments have been processed for those who secured their seats with credit 
cards, and checks were issued Friday for other ticket-buyers, a club spokesman 
said. The Kings did not make the playoffs, and their regular season ended on 
April 14. There is no NHL policy regarding the handling of playoff refunds. 
</P>
<P>
 The delay in postseason refunds has been a major point of contention for 
disgruntled King fans, who had been told they would receive their money shortly 
after the sale of the team closed on May 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
