<P>
TOTAL MECCA DEATH TOLL REACHES 829 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A total of 270 pilgrims died in a stampede during this week's symbolic 
"stoning the devil" ritual of the annual Muslim pilgrimage to Mecca, the 
government said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 An official statement released by the Saudi Press Agency said a total of 829 
people died during this year's hajj, or pilgrimage to Mecca, Islam's holiest 
city. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to the 270 people trampled in Monday's stampede, the toll included 
536 who died of natural causes such as sunstroke, old age or heart attack, and 
23 who died in several isolated accidents. 
</P>
<P>
 The government attributed the stampede to circumstances "beyond human 
endurance," noting that an all-time record of more than 2.5 million Muslims 
converged on Mecca for this year's rituals. Hospital sources and Asian 
diplomats earlier reported a much larger number of pilgrims killed in the 
stampede, with some putting the figure as high as 1,000. 
</P>
