<P>
 Benjamin L. Hooks, former executive director of the NAACP, stepped down Friday 
as chairman of the Leadership Conference on Civil Rights. 
</P>
<P>
 The conference has coordinated national campaigns that led to the enactment of 
several civil rights bills during the past 12 years. 
</P>
<P>
 A nominating committee is searching for a successor, officials said. 
</P>
