<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HOLIDAY CLOSINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monday is Memorial Day. The following schedule will be in effect: 
</P>
<P>
 * City, county, state and federal offices will be closed. 
</P>
<P>
 * County, state and federal courthouses will be closed. 
</P>
<P>
 * City and county libraries will be closed. 
</P>
<P>
 * Banks and savings and loans will be closed. Home Savings of America is also 
closed today. 
</P>
<P>
 * Schools, colleges and universities will be closed. Elementary and junior 
high schools in the Los Alamitos Unified School District will also be closed 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 * Mail: There will be no postal service. 
</P>
<P>
 * Trash: Trash will be collected one day late throughout the week, except in 
Anaheim and Orange. There, trash normally picked up on Monday will be collected 
on Tuesday, but the rest of the collection schedule will remain normal. 
</P>
<P>
 * Buses: OCTA buses will run on a Sunday schedule. 
</P>
<P>
 * Parks: All city- and county-run parks will be open during regular hours. 
</P>
</TEXT>
