ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; ELECTRONICS STORE, EMPLOYEES ROBBED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At least three armed men robbed a consumer electronics company Friday, 
handcuffing six employees and loading a rental truck with compact disc players, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The intruders came to Advanced Marketing and Distribution in the 16600 block 
of Noyes Avenue just after noon.They initially pretended to be interested in 
buying stereos, then pulled guns and handcuffed employees, Irvine Detective 
Larry Montgomery said. 
</P>
<P>
 Four of the employees were forced to lie on the floor of a front restroom, and 
two others were taken to a rear restroom, where they were robbed of wallets and 
rings. The employees were not injured, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The robbers then took an undetermined number of Sony compact disc players. The 
three men, possibly joined by a fourth, left the scene in two vehicles, heading 
south on Jamboree Road. 
</P>
</TEXT>
