<P>
NUDE GARDEN GROVE MAN ON ARIZ. FREEWAY SHOT AFTER ATTACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A nude Garden Grove man walking on Interstate 10 was shot Friday after 
attacking a highway patrol officer, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Ricci, 23, was listed in stable condition in a Phoenix hospital after 
being shot twice by Officer Mike Bynaker of the Arizona Department of Public 
Safety, a department spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Ricci apparently went berserk after being hailed by Bynaker. 
Officials didn't know why Ricci was nude, why he was on the highway or why he 
attacked the officer. 
</P>
<P>
 Bynaker had stopped to check an apparently abandoned truck on the highway 
about 12:45 a.m. when he saw Ricci walking in the highway's emergency lane in 
the nude. 
</P>
<P>
 Bynaker called to Ricci, who turned back and charged toward the officer, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Bynaker sprayed pepper spray on Ricci in an attempt to stop him and then began 
using his baton when Ricci continued his attack. 
</P>
<P>
 After Ricci grabbed the baton, Bynaker fired at him twice. The first shot hit 
Ricci in the chest after passing through one of his hands, and the other shot 
hit Ricci in the arm. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite the wounds, Ricci jumped toward the driver's side of Bynaker's patrol 
car and the officer slammed the door, inadvertently crushing the fingers of one 
of Ricci's hands. Bynaker then finally was able to handcuff Ricci, police said. 
</P>
