<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: WESTLAKE VILLAGE; ARTISTS' SALES TO AID CANCER 
SUPPORT UNIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PHYLLIS W. JORDAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Local artists will set up their easels and sell their work Sunday on a 
Westlake Village tennis court to raise money for a cancer support group. 
</P>
<P>
 As part of a continuing fund-raiser, the Wellness Community Valley / Ventura 
is sponsoring the art show on the grounds of the Emerald Forest Design House. 
</P>
<P>
 The house, a French chateau decorated by renowned designers and overlooking 
the North Ranch Country Club, has already drawn nearly 2,500 visitors since it 
opened in early May. The $15 house tour ends June 5. 
</P>
<P>
 A portion of the art sale proceeds, as well as the ticket revenues, will go to 
support the Wellness Community. 
</P>
<P>
 The group is dedicated to helping cancer patients cope with their illnesses. 
</P>
<P>
 The house on Oxley Road is a five-bedroom mansion with a sweeping staircase 
and marble foyer. 
</P>
<P>
 Its rooms were finished by 16 California interior designers, including Tony 
Duquette and Hutton Wilkinson. 
</P>
<P>
 The art show runs from noon to 5 p.m. Sunday and includes artist Neil Boyle 
and Mark Ivy. 
</P>
<P>
 The house tours begin at 10 a.m. Wednesday through Sunday. Doors close at 4 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets are available at the door or through Ticketmaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Groups can call 374-0022 for reservations. PHYLLIS W. JORDAN 
</P>
