<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; MAN FOUND INNOCENT IN MOTORIST'S DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 44-year-old Upland man was found not guilty Friday of misdemeanor vehicular 
manslaughter stemming from a 1992 traffic collision that killed a Port Hueneme 
man. 
</P>
<P>
 A Ventura County Municipal Court jury listened to eight days of testimony and 
deliberated two days before returning the not guilty verdict against Anthony 
Garcia. 
</P>
<P>
 Juan Alcantar Tapia, 51, was killed when his van collided head-on with a truck 
driven by Garcia near the entrance to a produce market at 3000 Hueneme Road, 
the California Highway Patrol said. The jury deadlocked 6 to 6 before clearing 
Garcia of any wrongdoing, Deputy Dist. Atty. Christopher S. Harman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia did not have any alcohol or drugs in his system, lawyers said. 
</P>
<P>
 Defense attorney George Eskin said prosecutors contended that Garcia was 
speeding and driving with defective brakes. But Eskin said that the wreck 
occurred on rain-slick streets in Oxnard and that a tractor-trailer parked on 
the road played a role in the incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was sticking out into the highway, and it was a factor in the accident," 
Eskin said. DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
