<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; 2 TEEN-AGERS HELD IN ROBBERY ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two 16-year-olds from Camarillo were arrested and charged with attempted armed 
robbery early Friday after approaching two skateboarders and demanding money, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 11 p.m. Thursday, two juveniles driving a Cadillac pulled up next to two 
20-year-old men skateboarding near Santa Rosa Road and Verdugo Way, and asked 
for their money while brandishing a revolver, according to Ventura County 
Sheriff's Sgt. Mike Barnes. 
</P>
<P>
 The skateboarders told them that they had no money, and the youths drove away 
empty-handed. The skateboarders memorized the car's license plate and called 
911. 
</P>
<P>
 Police found the abandoned Cadillac less than a mile away and traced the 
youths by contacting its owner. 
</P>
<P>
 They were arrested a few hours later. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
